quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  77,41,"The pious ones (that day) would be amidst cool shades, fountains"
  77,42,And fruits of their choice
  77,43,"Eat and drink, and relish your rewards! (It is yours) in return for what you used to do"
  77,44,This is really how We reward the righteous
  77,45,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,46,"(Oh unbelievers)! Eat and enjoy (your possessions) just a little while longer. Indeed, you are the criminals"
  77,47,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,48,"When asked to kneel (before their Lord), they refused"
  77,49,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,50,"So, after this (Qur´an), is there any other discourse they can (accept and) believe"